  "description": [
    "Page Three Treatment to Combat Rabies Developed ANTITOXIN IS SEEN AS CURE IN ACTIVE CASES Use Principle Now Successful in Diph theria Cases CHICAGOA new treatment for the prevention and cure of rabies has been developed at the county hospital it was announced last uight The treatment is the result of experiments by Dr Maurice L Blatt professor of childrens dis eases at the University of Illinois college of medicine and a member of the hospital staff and Dr Sam vel J Hoffman chief resident phy sician at the childrens hospital Have Developed Serum After more than a years research the physicians have developed a se rum which it is hoped will success fluly combat hydrophobia The prin ciple it was explained is the same ns that used for the treatment of scarlet fever and diphtheria cases in which the serum of an immunized animal is used to combat the dis ease in another animal or human The antitoxin prepared by Dr Blatt and Dr Hoffman has success fully halted the development of rabies in laboratory animalschief ly rabbitsbut as yet there has been no opportunity to test it as a therapeutic measure in a human case hospital officials said"
